            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9 billion request for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to advance peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities across Earth science, planetary exploration, and astrophysics\n* Sustains U.S. strategic leadership and sets exploration norms in direct competition with China's expanding lunar and Martian exploration ambitions\n* Supports the local aerospace industrial base and technical workforce, including CA-45 contractors such as Leach International Corp and Siemens Industry Software Inc.\n* Restores funding stability to protect the national STEM talent pipeline and agency workforce following the significant disruptions of the FY 2026 budget cycle",
